 including those generated by employees through NESSIE           My UI Info   Enables University employees to view employment-related information, such as benefits, policies, and training opportunities. Employees may also conduct personnel transactions online via secured self-service applications.  New Hire  New employee onboarding forms           Salary Planner   An interface for completing Annual Salary Changes for Budgeted Employees.           Tracker I-9   Overview  UIC Campus units use Tracker to electronically enter the Form I9 for all new hires and rehires for University employees. The system also checks E-Verify for employees who meet certain criteria.  Access  Access to HireTouch must be requested by unit security contacts (USC) Locate your USC  Online Training  Form I9 Basics (required for new users)  Tracker I9 Procedures (required for new users)  FAQ   When is Section 1 of the Form I-9 due?    When is Section 2 of the Form I-9 due?    What I-9s can I see?    What is a worksite?    How far in advance can the Form I-9 be initiated?    Is the UIN required when I create the employee profile?     Webinar Support  Tracker I-9 System Upgrade Webinar  Job Aids  Tracker Dashboard – Explanation of Tracker’s dashboard functionality.  Employee Profiles – Explanation of new Employee Profile feature.  Single-Use New Hire Login Email – Use a system-generated email to initiate the I-9.  One on One Method – For use at the I-9 Manager’s computer when new hire does not have access to a computer or the employee visits the unit to complete the I-9 form.  Remote Hire – For use when a remote hire is necessary           System Access   Access to the HR systems must be request by your unit security contact (USC).  Locate your USC                 HR STAFF & MANAGERS    Back to main content           Background Check Compliance    Compensation     About Academic Professionals     Academic Notices of Non-Reappointment      About Civil Service    About Grad Assistants     Minima for